Jordan -

     Yes, using an A-D-L would be a great idea if it was useful.  It
is not, however, due to the requirement that the domain name to the
right of the last "@" be defined to the Internet domain system.
Consequently A-D-L's are useless.

     That is why the TOPS-20 mailsystem doesn't implement A-D-L's,
except to correctly parse them and pass them on.  Actually, there is
a bug that causes it to expect an implementation of A-D-L's.  Mail
from PANDA (my DEC-2020 at home) shows up on the Internet with a
&gt;From address of MRC%PANDA@SUMEX-AIM.ARPA, however the Return-Path
shows up as @SUMEX-AIM.ARPA:MRC@PANDA.  This causes no end of jollies
to poor mailers all over the place which try to figure out what PANDA
is...some don't know at all, a few mis-guess it as being some other
PANDA, and a very very few actually do the A-D-L thing.  Someday I
might fix this.

-- Mark --
